article.description: Penn State beat up on another Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference team to tune up for a showdown on Sunday.
article.headline: Mazzante scores 25 points as Penn State rolls
article.linkText: Mazzante, Penn State crush another MAAC school
article.story:
FAIRFIELD, Conn. (Ticker) -- Penn State beat up on another Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference team to tune up for a showdown on Sunday.

Kelly Mazzante scored 25 points and Jessica Brungo added 17 as the 14th-ranked Lady Lions took a break from the Preseason WNIT with a 96-50 rout of Fairfield.

Penn State (4-0) has won three games in the Preseason WNIT to set up Sunday's final at No. 3 Kansas State. The Lady Lions tuned up by dominating a Stags team that was playing its season opener.

It was the second time that Penn State defeated an overmatched squad from the MAAC. The Lady Lions throttled Siena, 90-61, in the second round of the Preseason WNIT.

Ashli Scwab scored 12 points on 6-of-7 shooting and Tanisha Wright added 10 as Penn State shot 57 percent (35-of-61) and held a 47-32 rebounding edge.  Mazzante and Brungo each made three 3-pointers.

Schrene Isidora scored 23 points on 9-of-21 shooting and Cathy Dash added 11 for Fairfield (0-1). The Stags had just six assists.
